Paper: hep-th/9808103

Date: 1998-08-17

Title: Do anyons solve Heisenberg's Urgleichung in one dimension

Authors: N. Ilieva and W. Thirring

Comments: 19 pages LaTeX, to appear in Eur. Phys. J. C

Journal-ref: Eur.Phys.J. C6 (1999) 705-714

We construct solutions to the chiral Thirring model in the framework ofalgebraic quantum field theory. We find that for all positive temperaturesthere are fermionic solutions only if the coupling constant is $\lambda =\sqrt{2(2n + 1)\pi}, n \in \bf N$.